======================================================================
Decision of Judge Zefram:  TRUE

Kelly's analysis is exhaustive and convincing.  I see three primary
points to the argument:

(1) There can be no question that Morendil intended eir statement in
plaintiff's exhibit A to be interpreted as an accurate and complete
statement of the changes to the Regulations of Morendil's Feline
Orphanage.  Exhibits B and C, combined with the emoticon in exhibit A,
substantiate that.  Further, CFJ 827 establishes that the presumption
is generally to be that information posted to the Public Forum is
presented as correct.

(2) I agree with the plaintiff that the statement in exhibit A would be
interpreted by any reasonable Agoran as being presented as an accurate
and complete statement of the changes to the Regulations of MFO.  While
the phrasing used could, in some cases, be interpreted as merely a
vague description of, or even merely a comment upon, the Regulation
changes, I contend that such usage is primarily verbal.  Further, in
this case, a complete description would be expected; and even taking
the statement as a vague description, it omits to mention a major
feature of the changes to the Regulations.

For these reasons, I find that Morendil presented eir statement that
"regulations temp A) through temp D) have been Repealed" as correct,
within the meaning of TIA.  Further, e presented the implication that
no other changes were made at the same time as correct.

(3) Morendil's message reproduced in exhibit B is of much more rigorous
wording than exhibit A, and I therefore consider it more
authoritative.  It states, and to my mind establishes, that the changes
to the Regulations of MFO included the addition of "the Immaculate
Regulation".  I therefore find that the Regulation Amendments in
question were of the nature implied by exhibit B, in contrast to the
statement in exhibit A.

Therefore, Morendil committed the Crime of Misrepresentation on 20th
April 1996, in posting the message reproduced as exhibit A.

