======================================================================
Decision of Justice Steve:  FALSE

I overturn Zefram's Judgement, finding the Statement FALSE. Although
there was nothing wrong with Judge Zefram's reasoning from his
premises, I am now convinced that these premises were mistaken in
fact. However, Judge Zefram is not to be held responsible for this
error, since Morendil's statements up to the time Zefram delivered
his Judgement were ambiguous, and it is only through having sought
and obtained subsequent clarification from Morendil in the form of a
sworn affidavit in the Public Forum, that it has been possible to
resolve the ambiguity.  

Morendil's new testimony (in Exhibit E, see Evidence attached) does
not contradict any of his prior statements; it merely resolves an
ambiguity in them. Therefore we have no reason to doubt its veracity.
That testimony indicates that the Immaculate Regulation was added to
the Regulations of Morendil's Feline Orphanage only after his post to
the Public Forum announcing the deletion of the Temporary Regulations. 
Hence that post did not mislead by suggesting, as alleged, that an
amendment (the addition of the Immaculate Regulation) had not
occurred which had in fact occurred. It could not so mislead, since
the amendment in question had not yet been effected. Hence I Judge
the Statement FALSE.

Steve Gardner                     |  Some people lose their sense of
Dept. of Philosophy, Monash Uni.  |  perspective. I've lost my sense
gardner@aurora.cc.monash.edu.au   |  of scale.          -- Will Self

======================================================================
Decision of Justice ElJefe:  FALSE

I judge FALSE.

According to Morendil's chronology of events, he changed the regs
to include "the Immaculate regulation" after Message A and before 
Message B. Thus the information presented in the message to the PF 
(A) was believed by Morendil to be correct, and was in fact correct 
at the time it was sent.

I remark that Morendil's other evidence (Message D) gave the impression 
(though without explicitly stating it) that the Immaculate Regulation was 
inserted before Message A.  It claimed that Players could have used 
Rule 1064 to request the Regs (including the Immaculate one) after being 
notified (by Message A) that the Regs had changed.

This cannot have been true the first few moments moment after Message A 
was sent, because assuming Morendil's Chronology there was a gap between 
Message A and the creation of the Immaculate Regulation.  I do believe that 
it was just this phrasing in Message D that led to this CFJ.

Does Message D violate Rule 1497?  I don't believe so.  It's not a Crime
to be confused.

